Very good. I doubled the apples and halved the sugar. Left it chunky and ate it while it was still hot. I drizzled a few drops of heavy cream over each serving. It adds a miniscule amount of fat and a little creaminess.

Rating: 4
As quick and easy as it looks. I like to leave the peel on  it's easier, and makes the texture more interesting. To adapt for the Crock Pot, reduce water to 1/3 cup and cook on low for 5 - 6 hours.

Rating: 4
As with many others, this was my first time making applesauce (which amazes me, because I absolutely love apples and this time of year). And with most of the reviews, this is absolutely fantastic. Simple, and delicious--I made exactly as written and pureed the final product in a food processor (I don't like chunky applesauce). My niece and sister and brother-in-law loved it, and they are sometimes tough critics. I'm making my second batch now (less than 1 week later).

Rating: 4
Amazing! My 1st try at homemade applesauce. Used 5 Honeycrisps & 1 Macintosh, 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1 cup water. Took a long time (30 min) for all the water to evaporate, but well worth it.

