I forgot to add that I used Pumpkin Pie seasoning rather than just cinnamon. Like an earlier reviewer, I'll never buy applesauce from a jar again! The recipe says it can be prepared a few days in advance. Be careful though, if your house is like mine, it will be gone before the day is over.

Rating: 4
I made this recipe for Christmas Eve. It's New Year's day and I've made it three times since! Everyone has loved it. I've made it with Gala and Golden Delicious and will try other varieties too. Family, friends and babies have loved it. I made it once without lemon and it made no real difference. I served it at room temp and without pureeing the apples. It's helped me to eat fewer desserts over the holidays too. (Think I'll go make some now!)

Rating: 4
I can only reiterate what everyone else has written: simple recipe, fantastic applesauce and I'll never buy it from the store again. I used almost 4 1/2 four pounds of Jonagold apples but the same measurements for the other ingredients except the cinnamon, which I doubled. I also dark brown sugar rather than the light in the recipe didn't add any lemon juice as I discovered I didn't have any, but no one missed it. I pureed it before adding the cinnamon as my kids don't like chunky applesauce. They sure love this!

